## 2 Sample Dependent T-Test using Long Data  ##
################################################

#If you attempt to run a dependent 2 sample t-test using long data using the
#linear model lm() function setting paired = TRUE such as in the example below,
#you will receive an error:
results2 <- lm(happy ~ book, data=bookhappy, paired = TRUE)

#Reason: One of the assumptions of running a linear model is that the
#observations are independent of one another. In this case, when we set paired =
#TRUE, RStudio understands that the observations are not independent but rather
#that there is dependency. As such, it is not able to run a linear model on
#dependent data. Therefore, if our data is shaped long and we must run a
#dependent two sample t-test, we must reshape the data to wide and use the
#t.test() function

